commText: Welcome back. MI as expected have got their impact sub in Rohit Sharma. Nuwan Thushara is chilling as he is subbed out. Munching on his dinner I suppose having changed into his training gear. Arora has the new-ball. A wide slip in.

50-plus IPL wickets at a venue 69 - Sunil Narine (Kolkata) 68 - Lasith Malinga (Mumbai WS) 58 - Amit Mishra (Delhi) 52 - Yuzvendra Chahal (Bengaluru) 51 - Jasprit Bumrah (Mumbai WS) Venkatesh Iyer vs MI Inns: 5 Runs: 320 Avg: 80 SR: 161.61 50s/100s: 3/1 HS: 104 Most hauls of 3 wickets or more in the IPL 23 - Jasprit Bumrah (131 innings) 20 - Yuzvendra Chahal (154 innings) 19 - Lasith Malinga (122 innings) 17 - Amit Mishra (162 innings)

Piyush Chawla: The wicket was a bit stopping at the start, it’s a fresh wicket so it was a bit sticky, but no matter how it plays you have to bowl well. The way we bowled today it was really great to see. Well, at the end of the day, it totally depends on what the team requires, that time Hardik came and bowled a really good over. It looks like there is a bit of dew out there and it will play a little better.

21:15 Local Time, 15:45 GMT, 21:15 IST: Good comeback from KKR to end on 169. And for that they have to thank Venkatesh Iyer a lot. Nuwan Thushara took the first three and then Pandya and Chawla chipped in to leave KKR at 57/5. KKR had no other option but to use their batting impact sub and out came Manish Pandey. Pandey and Iyer resurrected the innings with a 83-run stand and the stage was set for DreRuss to explode. He started with a six but was run-out after a mix-up which potentially cost KKR 20 runs. Bumrah was outstanding at the death as he mopped up the innings with a three-fer. The end overs acceleration did not come and what looked like 190 has turned out to be 169. Advantage MI but this pitch is sticky and it's holding a bit. The spinners will definitely come into play and KKR have two gun ones. Back for the chase in 5 minutes...

Bumrah to Venkatesh Iyer, out Bowled!! Bumrah too good. Venkatesh Iyer tries to do something different, shuffles across outside off and this is a missile at middle stump, Venkatesh Iyer misses the scoop and the middle-stump is flattened. Bumrah ends things. Venkatesh Iyer b Bumrah 70(52) [4s-6 6s-3]

Bumrah to Ramandeep Singh, out Caught by Gerald Coetzee!! Last ball he tries this and failed, now he finds third man. Short outside off, Ramandeep Singh ramps and Coetzee initially did not pick it, then comes forward to take it well. Ramandeep Singh c Gerald Coetzee b Bumrah 2(4)

Hardik Pandya to Venkatesh Iyer, out Russell Run Out!! Poor from Russell and he has to go. But should Venkatesh Iyer have sacrificed himself? Full outside the leg-stump, Iyer reverse-sweeps and finds short third man, Russell was not looking and just ran, Iyer was watching the ball after initially taking a few steps down the wicket, then he suddenly sees Russell near him, sends him back and it's too late, despite the throw wide of the stumps on the bounce, Hardik Pandya did really well to collect and then turn around to break the stumps, was not easy but he managed to find the stumps. How much will this cost KKR? Russell just runs off, must be seething for sure. Russell run out (N Thushara/Hardik Pandya) 7(2) [6s-1]
Hardik Pandya to Venkatesh Iyer, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!
Russell is gone. Run-out. What a massive moment.

Hardik Pandya to Venkatesh Iyer, SIX, good hit. Hardik Pandya follows Venkatesh Iyer outside the leg-stump with a full delivery, but the batter flicks and it's over wide long-on, did well to get under that

The slower ball off-cutter works this time, holds up on a fullish length and Manish Pandey in trying to slog, miscues it totally, one hand comes off and Brevis the sub runs forward from extra-cover to take a simple catch. MI on top and are enjoying the proceedings. Narine b Hardik Pandya 8(8) [6s-1]

The ball is holding up a bit on this pitch and the KKR batters are not being able to come to terms with it! 132kph full length ball attacking the stumps, swings in a bit, Shreyas Iyer flicks it and is not in control of his shot as the ball flies to the right of David at mid-on. N Thushara to Philip Salt, out Caught by Tilak Varma!! Good awareness from Tilak Varma and MI have got the important breakthrough! A back of a length ball angling in, Philip Salt walks down the track and tries to hit it across but only manages to get a leading edge over point. Tilak runs towards it and so does Naman Dhir from the deep. Tilak does well to keep his eyes on the ball and takes a good catch. Naman almost collided with him but he did well to keep his composure.
